---
title: Reading List
description: My personal reading list.
image: /img/reading.png
layout: page.njk
permalink: /reading/index.html
---
<div class="grid grid2 gap2 mt2">
  <div>
    <img src="/img/reading.png" class="img-center img-fluid m0" alt="An illustration, taken from undraw.co, showing a female person reading a book while sitting in a chair">
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      These are the most recent items added to my reading list in Raindrop.io. The books I'm reading won't appear on this page - they're usually listed on my <a href="/now/">/now page</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="m0">
      The list below gets updated on every new build of this website, and it was last updated on {% buildDate true %}.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="hr shadow mt2 mb1"></div>
{% if reading | length %}
  <ul class="list-reset">
    {% for item in reading %}
      <li class="py1" {% if loop.last %} style="padding-bottom: 0 !important;"{% endif %}>
        <h2 class="h5">
          {{ item.title }}
        </h2>
        <ul class="list-reset text-muted small">
          <li>
            Saved: <time class="dt-published" datetime="{{ item.saved | date('YYYY-MM-DD') }}">{{ item.saved | date('MMMM DD, YYYY') }}</time> from {{ item.domain }}
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin: .5rem 0;">
          {{ item.description }}
        </p>
        <p class="m0">
          &ndash;&nbsp;<a class="ext" href="{{ item.url }}" rel="noopener nofollow">Read Now</a>
        </p>
        {% if not loop.last %}
          <div class="hr shadow mt2 mb0"></div>
        {% endif %}
      </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
{% else %}
  <p>No data :(</p>
{% endif %}
